org.apache.felix.ipojo.extender.internal

Interface BundleProcessor

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Lifecycle
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChainedBundleProcessor, ComponentsBundleProcessor, ConfigurationProcessor, ExtensionBundleProcessor, ForwardingBundleProcessor, QueuingActivationProcessor, ReverseBundleProcessor

    public interface BundleProcessor
extends Lifecycle
    Main Processor interface. A bundle processor is an extender fragment, it analyzes the bundle content and creates the entities.

    Notice the difference between the activate / deactivate methods called when a bundle is starting and stopping, and start / stop called when the iPOJO bundle is started and stopped.
